1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
An agent brain, built from ops runbooks —
but someone ingested a secret launch code.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:15,000
A leaked secret is recallable, even across paraphrases.
Memory CI catches it — the build fails.

3
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:22,500
forget() the secret, surgically.
One node-set, nothing else.

4
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:31,000
Unrecallable across every probe —
and every runbook fact still intact.

5
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:36,000
A forget-regression test: proof, on every
change, that the secret is gone.

6
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Now watch it happen in the graph —
an AI un-remembering, on command.

7
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:46,000
LEAK turns to SOBER.
The secret's subgraph just dissolved.

8
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:59,000
And git bisect for a poisoned brain —
the bad batch, localized in O(log n).

9
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:04,000
SOBER — your brain can't merge a regression anymore.
github.com/wiz-abhi/SOBER
